Indian Fishermen Arriving From Pakistan Sunday
NEW DELHI , November 22 ( Xinhua ) -- All the 190 Indian fishermen released by Pakistan are expected to enter Indian waters Sunday , Defense Ministry sources said here .
A coast guard ship " Sangram " has been deployed at the International Border Line ( IBL ) in the Arabian Sea to escort the returning fishermen on board 31 boats to Okha harbor in Gujarat of southwestern India .
The fishermen had been detained by Pakistan for straying into Pakistani waters while fishing in the Arabian Sea .
Earlier this year India also released 148 Pakistan fishermen and 15 boats detained by it for the same reason .
Both sides welcomed the decision of the respective governments to release fishermen in each other 's custody .
